# CIDD_GRID_DATA.INFO:  Parameters for gridded Data
#
# Desc = Field Description- Should be unique ID - Used for ID'ing contour and grid overlay fields in other
#        parameter files. 
# Label = Label used in menus, popups and legends
# host = Computer hostname or IP address of the server for this data field
# port = TCP/IP Port the server resides on
# Field = Numerical Index of the field in the files that the server reads
# Color_file = Name of the color scale description file
# units = String used to label the colorscale
# Cont-lo-hi-interv = Three Numerical values describing the default base, top and interval of contours
# format = Rendering method - "cart" = filled rectangles, "cont" = filled contours
#                           - append "_comp" to generate a composite request, ie. cart_comp, etc
#
# S_type = Server Type Should be "Cidd", depreciated type; "Radial"
# S_subtype = Server Subtype - Often refers to the underlying Data format. Usually now "MDV"
# S_inst = Server Instance - A String used to determine HOST/PORT pairs when utilizing the Server mapper
#
# Disp = Display this field by default in the field menus and popups - Diagnostic fields often have this set =0
# Rend = Background Render - IE. Automatically generate an image for this field - Interacts with the HTML MODE
#            Set this field to 1 when you want this field rendered before a user selects it. This makes it
#            "Instantly" available, for "toggling". Set this to 1 for any fields you want automatically
#            output when CIDD is operating in HTML MODE.
#  
